         <abstract>
            <p>If $p$ is an irregular prime, $p &lt; 8000$, then the indices $2n$ for which the Bernoulli quotients $B_{2n}/2n$ are divisible by $p^2$ are completely characterized. In particular, it is always true that $2n &gt; p$ and that $B_{2n}/2n \not\equiv (B_{2n+p-1}/2n + p - 1) (\operatorname{mod} p^2)$ if $(p, 2n)$ is an irregular pair. As a result, we obtain another verification that the cyclotomic invariants $\mu_p$ of Iwasawa all vanish for primes $p &lt; 8000$.</p>
          </abstract>
